cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.SE 

The paper discusses a new type of clogging DoS attacks using off-path TCP injections, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attacks also involve network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system engineering (cs.SY) as they target backbone connections and require modular construction. The paper also mentions the use of cryptography for security, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
